                                <expan>vernom<ex>en</ex></expan> und ist uns
                            <expan>bish<ex>er</ex></expan> niht wissend davon
                                <expan>gewes<ex>en</ex></expan>. Doch wenn
                            <expan>uns<ex>er</ex></expan> hawbtlewt <expan>h<ex>er</ex></expan> heim
                                <expan>kome<ex>n</ex></expan>, so <expan>welle<ex>n</ex></expan> wir
                        ir rede <expan>daru<ex>m</ex>b</expan>
<expan>g<ex>er</ex>n</expan> hören. Denn wo wir
                            <expan>ewr<ex>er</ex></expan>
<expan>erberk<ex>eit</ex></expan> lieb <expan>od<ex>er</ex></expan> dienst
                        etc. <expan>Dat<ex>um</ex></expan>
<expan>ip<ex>s</ex>a</expan> die <expan>s<ex>an</ex>c<ex>t</ex>i</expan>
